summary:
Richard Nixon:  Look, when you're in office you gotta do a lot of things 
sometimes that are not always in the strictest sense...
caption:
Richard Nixon:  Look, when you’re in office you gotta do a lot of things sometimes that are not always in the strictest sense of the law, legal, but you do them because they’re in the greater interest of the nation.

David Frost: Alright wait, wait just so I understand correctly, are you really saying that in certain situations the President can decide whether it’s in the best interest of the nation and then do something illegal…

Richard Nixon: I’m saying that when the President does it, that means it’s *not* illegal!

David Frost: I’m sorry?

summary: Jon Hamm, David Tennant, Michael Sheen Perform Dueling Hamlets
body:
Jon Hamm, David Tennant, Michael Sheen Perform Dueling Hamlets

The “Good Omens” gang performed dueling Hamlets at NYCC2018, where Michael Sheen and David Tennant played opposite Jon Hamm as two charismatic Hamlets and an overly handsome Ophelia. It turned out, unsurprisingly, the dorky “a couple of angels and a demon” mixture made quite a dream cast for Hamlet the play.

P.S. My personal favorite, besides the cold open, was David mildly complaining that he only had one line while Michael got to say all the good ones.

title: Apostle (2018)
body:

Just this past Friday, Netflix also released the period horror film Apostle just in time for Halloween, and it did not disappoint. The first half of Apostleis very tame and mysterious, and the latter half spirals…

summary: “God does not play dice with the universe; He plays an ineffable game of His own devising, which might be compared, from the...
caption: “God does not play dice with the universe; He plays an ineffable game of His own devising, which might be compared, from the perspective of any of the other players, to being involved in an obscure and complex variant of poker in a pitch-dark room, with blank cards, for infinite stakes, with a Dealer who won’t tell you the rules, and who smiles all the time.” - Terry Pratchett, Good Omens: The Nice and Accurate Prophecies of Agnes Nutter, Witch
